html
  head
    meta(charset='UTF-8')
    title=title
    link(rel='stylesheet prefetch', href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Noto+Sans:700')
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='/stylesheets/style.css')
    link(rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/component.css')
    link(rel='stylesheet' type='text/css' href='https://cdn.rawgit.com/dreampulse/computer-modern-web-font/master/fonts.css')

  
  body
    include header

    div.container
      div.jumbotron
        ul(class="input-list style-1 clearfix")
          li
            h1 Garch
          li
            p The generalized autoregressive conditional heteroskedasticity (GARCH) process is an econometric term that describes an approach to estimate volatility in financial markets. The GARCH process is often preferred by financial modeling professionals because it provides a more real-world context than other forms when trying to predict the prices and rates of financial instruments.

      div.jumbotron
        ul(class="input-list style-1 clearfix")
          li
            input(type="text", name='ticker', placeholder=":ticker")
          li
            input(type="text", name='startDate', placeholder=":start date (yyyy-mm-dd)")
          li
            input(type="text", name='endDate', placeholder=":end date (yyyy-mm-dd)")
          li
            button(class="btn btn-1 btn-1a", id='calculate') Calculate
        div.loading
          img(id='loading-image', src='images/ajax-loader.gif', alt='Loading...')
        div.popup
          p #{response}
          img(#{src})

    include footer

    script(src='http://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/2.1.3/jquery.min.js').
    script(src='/javascripts/script.js').
